---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Yoghurt of Youth"
  description="How Yoghurt of Youth collects, uses, and protects your personal data, and your rights under UK data protection law."
>
  <section
    id="privacy"
    class="relative scroll-mt-32 md:scroll-mt-24 bg-white text-slate-800 py-12"
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-xs">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-GB", { day: "numeric", month: "long", year: "numeric" })}</p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        This policy explains how <strong>Yoghurt of Youth</strong> collects, uses,
        and protects your personal data when you visit our website or place an
        order, and sets out your rights under UK data protection law (the UK GDPR
        and the Data Protection Act 2018).
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Who we are</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Yoghurt of Youth is a sole trader business based in the United Kingdom. We
        are the "data controller" responsible for your personal data. You can
        contact us at:
      </p>
      <div class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <p>Yoghurt of Youth</p>
        <p>11 Billinge Avenue, Blackburn, Lancashire, BB2 6SD</p>
        <p>Email: <a href="mailto:support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-amber-500 transition">support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk</a></p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">What data we collect</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Depending on how you interact with us, we may collect:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li><strong>Order information</strong> — your name, delivery address, email address, and phone number, so we can process and deliver your order.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information</strong> — card and billing details, which are collected and processed securely by our payment provider, Stripe. We do not store your full card details ourselves.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing information</strong> — your email address, if you sign up to our mailing list or discount offers.</li>
        <li><strong>Website usage information</strong> — data collected through cookies and similar technologies when you browse our site, such as pages visited and general activity, used for analytics and advertising.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">How we use your data, and our lawful bases</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">We use your data only where we have a lawful basis to do so:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li><strong>To fulfil your order</strong> (processing payment, arranging delivery, sending order confirmations). Lawful basis: performance of a contract.</li>
        <li><strong>To send you marketing emails</strong> (offers, updates, and product information), where you have signed up. Lawful basis: your consent, which you can withdraw at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>To improve our website and advertising</strong> through analytics and marketing tools. Lawful basis: our legitimate interests in running and promoting our business.</li>
        <li><strong>To meet legal obligations</strong>, such as keeping records for tax and accounting. Lawful basis: legal obligation.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Who we share your data with</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        We use trusted third-party service providers ("processors") to run our
        business. We only share the data necessary for each service, and these
        providers are bound to protect it. They include:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — secure payment processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Klaviyo</strong> — email marketing and mailing list management.</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> — sending order confirmations and other transactional emails.</li>
        <li><strong>Meta (Facebook/Instagram)</strong> — advertising and measuring the performance of our ads.</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — website hosting.</li>
        <li><strong>Upstash</strong> — secure data storage supporting our website's functions.</li>
        <li><strong>DPD</strong> — delivery of your order.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Some of these providers may process data outside the UK. Where they do, we
        rely on their appropriate safeguards (such as standard contractual clauses)
        to protect your data. We do not sell your personal data to anyone.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">How long we keep your data</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        We keep your data only as long as necessary for the purposes above. Order
        and transaction records are kept for as long as required by law (for
        example, tax records are generally kept for six years). Marketing data is
        kept until you unsubscribe or ask us to remove it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">Under UK data protection law, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-slate-700">
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li>Ask us to correct data that is inaccurate or incomplete.</li>
        <li>Ask us to delete your data, where there is no ongoing reason to keep it.</li>
        <li>Object to, or ask us to restrict, certain processing.</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent to marketing at any time (every marketing email includes an unsubscribe link).</li>
        <li>Request a copy of your data in a portable format.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        To exercise any of these rights, email us at
        <a href="mailto:support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-amber-500 transition">support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk</a>.
        You also have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office
        (ICO), the UK's data protection regulator, at
        <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline hover:text-amber-500 transition">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Our website uses cookies and similar technologies, including the Meta Pixel
        and Klaviyo's onsite tracking, to understand how visitors use our site and
        to measure and improve our advertising. You can control cookies through your
        browser settings. We will continue to develop our cookie controls over time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on
        this page with a revised "last updated" date.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        If you have any questions about this policy or how we handle your data,
        please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk" class="underline hover:text-amber-500 transition">support@yoghurtofyouth.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>